subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalic cage chaetae damaged, as long as 1/3 body length (about half as long in some 
paratypes
), or about four times longer than body width. Chaetigers 1–2 involved in the cephalic cage; chaetiger 3 with chaetae longer than those present in following chaetigers, but not contributing to the cage. Chaetae arranged in short, ventrolateral rows; chaetiger 1 with 4 noto- (
8 in
paratypes
), and 8 neurochaetae, chaetiger 2 with 4 noto- and 4 neurochaetae per bundle.
